{
  "doc_id": "58102",
  "text": "Another important related work is [CITATION_1] by Legrand and Nicoloyannis who proposed a feature selection method based on preference aggregation. The method uses preferences aggregation to determine an ordered list of features subsets. The criteria in the preferences aggregation can be flexibly defined by users for finding an optimal features subset by filter-and-wrapper approaches. The logics of the algorithm can be extended to work on AVT with multi-resolution levels.",
